  "body": "I'm using K8S 1.10 and have a specific use case where I'm trying to use an emptyDir to share mounts between two containers in a pod.\r\nI'm using the MountPropagation feature successfully, but while debugging another issue I noticed that the node was running a very long running du command.\r\nLooking into the source I noted:\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/7f23a743e8c23ac6489340bbb34fa6f1d392db9d/pkg/volume/util/fs/fs.go\r\n\r\nWhich runs du on any emptyDir, do measure disk usage. I recommend that in this case we should add the -x flag that will skip any mounted directories as they do not count against the file usage and would make these scans a lot faster.\r\n\r\nI could of course add a simple pull request for this but first wanted to see if this was known and on purpose.\r\n\r\nTo reproduce bind mount/loop mount/device mount any large/slow directory into an emptyDir volume and watch as the du process slogs away\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes 1.10\r\n- GKE\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- DO NOT EDIT BELOW THIS LINE -->\r\n/kind bug",
